				<small>Monday, November 29th, 2010</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;"><a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-via="tradewithdave" data-count="vertical" data-url="http://tradewithdave.com/?p=3775">Tweet</a></div>
<p><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/53/AirrailFrankfurtAirport.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p>(photo: KPMG&#8217;s European office in Frankfurt, also known as the great silver frankurter)</p>
<p>To read the full report on the International Recovery Plan for Ireland produced by the fine folks at the Swiss Cooperative known as KPMG, links below:</p>
<p>The detailed report/budget at 140 pages in length: <a href="http://www.kpmg.ie/budget2011/deptdocs/docs/NationalRecoveryPlan/NationalRecoveryPlan.pdf">http://www.kpmg.ie/budget2011/deptdocs/docs/NationalRecoveryPlan/NationalRecoveryPlan.pdf</a></p>
